title: Baffert's National Treasure wins Preakness, hours after another horse was euthanized
description: Bob Baffert’s National Treasure has won the Preakness Stakes, hours after another of the Hall of Famer's horses was euthanized on the track with a racing injury

title: Volcanic ash from Popocatepetl temporarily shuts down Mexico City airports
description: Mexico City’s two main airports temporarily resumed operations after shutting down for a few hours due to ash spewing from Popocatepetl volcano, located 45 miles southeast of the country’s capital

title: British novelist Martin Amis, who brought a rock ‘n’ roll sensibility to his work, has died at 73
description: Amis brought a rock ‘n’ roll sensibility to his stories and lifestyle.

title: Songwriter Pete Brown, who co-wrote 'Sunshine of Your Love' and 'White Room,' dies at 82.
description: Poet and songwriter co-wrote some hit songs for the rock supergroup Cream.

title: Horse trained by Bob Baffert euthanized on track after racing injury on Preakness undercard
description: The horse went down with an injury during a race on the Preakness undercard.

title: Mother accused of abandoning newborn found alive in woods denied bond
description: A woman accused of abandoning her newborn in the woods nearly four years ago has been denied bond after prosecutors argued she could intimate potential witnesses.

title: Sinn Fein on course to be largest party in Northern Ireland local elections
description: Irish nationalist party is set to take the most seats in local elections.

title: Shark in Florida Keys bites angler who reeled it in, sending man to hospital
description: Authorities in the Florida Keys say a shark bit the foot of a fisherman.

title: DeSantis asks that judge be disqualified from Disney's free speech lawsuit
description: He claims judge's prior statements have raised questions about his impartiality.

title: Judge: Mississippi school can make trans girl dress as boy for graduation
description: A federal judge says he will not block the Mississippi school district.

title: F-18 fighter jet accident at Zaragoza airbase as pilot ejects successfully
description: The Spanish defense ministry says an F-18 fighter jet has crashed at an airbase in the Spanish city of Zaragoza but the pilot ejected successfully

title: 3-year-old shoots 2 people, leading to arrest of man wanted for murder
description: A shooting after a three-year-old accessed a gun led to the arrest of a murder suspect in Indiana on Thursday.

title: G7 urges China to press Russia to end war in Ukraine, respect Taiwan's status, fair trade rules
description: The Group of Seven wealthy democracies have urged China to push Russia to end its war on Ukraine

title: WATCH:  The story behind viral video of Swifties who became friends over chronic illness
description: Emma Sides, a student from Texas, connected with Madison Bernard, a student from Louisiana, online in 2021. They finally met in person at a Taylor Swift concert on April 22, 2023.

title: WATCH:  Jim Brown, NFL hall of famer and activist, dies at 87
description: The former Cleveland Browns player died in his LA home, according to his wife.

title: Nebraska bill bans gender-affirming care for trans minors, restricts abortion
description: The bill will restrict abortion after 12 weeks and gender affirming care for minors under the age of 19 in Nebraska.

title: Man who rushed Vatican City gate sent for psychiatric care at nearby hospital
description: The man who drove through one of the gates to Vatican City has been taken to a nearby hospital for psychiatric care

title: Massachusetts US Attorney Rachael Rollins formally resigns in wake of ethics probes
description: Massachusetts U.S. Attorney Rachael Rollins has formally resigned after wide-ranging investigations by two federal watchdog agencies found she sought to use her position to influence a local election and lied to investigators

title: Debt ceiling talks end after briefly resuming, negotiator says
description: After a day of stalled negotiations, House Speaker Kevin McCarthy said that negotiators will be "back in the room tonight" to continue working on a debt deal.

title: Reactions to the death of Jim Brown, NFL star, social activist and actor
description: The sports world reacts to the announcement that Jim Brown, an NFL star, social activist and actor, has died at the age of 87
